sentences: Brenton Weyi (born January 16, 1990) is an American essayist, thinker, playwright, poet, and humanist.
In 2014, Weyi became an early adopter of the sharing economy, becoming a champion for Airbnb.
In 2015, Weyi joined Playback Theatre West, Colorado's longest-running improvisational theatre company, which uses theater an empathy-building tool.
In 2016, he began tapping into his background to create art around the challenges and beauty in the Central African region.
In 2019, Weyi was a featured storyteller of Denver's edition of the Empathy Museum, a travelling pop-up that encourages members of the public to walk in each other's shoes.
In 2016, Weyi began work on a stage musical focusing on Congolese independence in the backdrop of the Cold War named My Country, My Country.
